.TH "axienet_set_mac_address" 9 "axienet_set_mac_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
axienet_set_mac_address \- Write the MAC address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" axienet_set_mac_address
.BI "(struct net_device *ndev "  ","
.BI "const void *address "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ndev" 12
Pointer to the net_device structure
.IP "address" 12
6 byte Address to be written as MAC address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called to initialize the MAC address of the Axi Ethernet
core. It writes to the UAW0 and UAW1 registers of the core.
